The paper deals with image restoration tasks, specifically image dehazing and deraining, which are commonly studied in the computer vision community. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The proposed method also involves the use of a deep neural network, which falls under the scope of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also mentions the use of a gated sub-network, which is a type of attention mechanism commonly used in deep learning models, and thus cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also a possible sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of dilation techniques to remove gridding artifacts, which falls under the scope of cs.GR (Graphics). Finally, the paper deals with image processing tasks, which is a common topic in cs.MM (Multimedia).
